<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 28 at 1:49PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Scattered snow showers will impact portions of North-Central
Montana through late this afternoon...
Scattered snow showers are developing over Meagher, Judith Basin,
and Fergus counties this afternoon. Snow showers may contain
brief heavy bursts of snow, gusty winds up to 40 mph, and possibly
a lightning strike or two. The heavier showers may produce
accumulations up to a half inch, along with brief periods of
reduced visibility and slippery roads.
Anyone traveling or outdoors should be alert to changing weather
conditions, especially over hilltops and ridges.</description>
